Yook Sung-jae (Korean: 육성재; Hanja: 陸星材; born (1995-05-02)May 2, 1995), better known mononymously as Sungjae, is a South Korean singer, songwriter, actor, host and entertainer.

Aside from his group's activities, Yook has acted in television dramas Plus Nine Boys (2014), Who Are You: School 2015 (2015), The Village: Achiara's Secret (2015), Guardian: The Lonely and Great God (2016) and Mystic Pop-up Bar (2020) and has appeared on hit shows, including: Hitmaker, We Got Married and Master in the House.

Aside from his group's activities, Yook has acted in television dramas Plus Nine Boys (2014), Who Are You: School 2015 (2015), The Village: Achiara's Secret (2015), Guardian: The Lonely and Great God (2016) and Mystic Pop-up Bar (2020) and has appeared on hit shows, including: Hitmaker, We Got Married and Master in the House.

Aside from his group's activities, Yook has acted in television dramas Plus Nine Boys (2014), Who Are You: School 2015 (2015), The Village: Achiara's Secret (2015), Guardian: The Lonely and Great God (2016) and Mystic Pop-up Bar (2020) and has appeared on hit shows, including: Hitmaker, We Got Married and Master in the House.

Aside from his group's activities, Yook has acted in television dramas Plus Nine Boys (2014), Who Are You: School 2015 (2015), The Village: Achiara's Secret (2015), Guardian: The Lonely and Great God (2016) and Mystic Pop-up Bar (2020) and has appeared on hit shows, including: Hitmaker, We Got Married and Master in the House.
Yook released his debut solo album, Yook O'Clock, on March 2, 2020.
Yook was born on May 2, 1995, in Yongin, Gyeonggi Province.
